--[ README ]-------------------------------------------------------------------
  
  Any script from current folder can be used via symbolic link that can be
  created with command:

    ln -s <source_script> <link_name>

  Scripts are designed to be run from the very top of the project tree. Make
  sure you have put links to next commonly used scripts:

    ScriptName      |       LinkName
    ----------------+------------------------
    print_error.sh  | bash_print_error.sh
    print_note.sh   | bash_print_note.sh
    print_usage.sh  | bash_print_usage.sh

  It is a best practise to put links to these scripts to some folder (say 
  {FOLDER1}} and add {FOLDER1} to $PATH:

    bash: export PATH="{FOLDER1}:$PATH"
    tcsh: setenv PATH "{FOLDER1}:$PATH"

  Good luck



